Functor Early into learning Haskell, we’re introduced to the Functor typeclass and how to fmap our way around with it. fmap is a structure-preserving operation that lets us transform the value wrapped by the structure:
class Functor f where fmap :: (a -&gt; b) -&gt; f a -&gt; f b Maybe has a Functor instance:
maybeFunctor :: Maybe Int -&gt; Maybe String maybeFunctor mInt = fmap show mInt [] also has a Functor instance:
